This paper is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category as it presents a method for improving the accuracy of neural ranking models in search engines. Additionally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) as it deals with document representations and expansion terms. Machine learning (cs.LG) is also relevant as the approach involves learned attention and end-to-end learning. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible sub-category as the paper involves a neural network-based approach. Finally, cybersecurity and privacy (cs.CY) may also be relevant as the paper deals with user feedback and document popularity, which could have implications for privacy and security in search engines.
